{"author":{"id":"2fec99dc79e1c05dcc8e6b4c2ef3b9c29fe62a9801fe4df49021516fba017977"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774360258,"nonce":"QxGdYAR243X8xP3kydZPl4/BE7Q=","title":"review: patch list not scrollable with mouse on large series","message":"Chris Samuel reports that the patch list on the left side of the review\nTUI cannot be scrolled with the mouse when the series is large (e.g. 40\npatches).\n\nThe #patch-list ListView uses height: auto in its CSS, which causes it\nto expand beyond its container instead of scrolling within it. The\ntracking list uses height: 1fr correctly.\n\nAdditionally, action_prev_patch/action_next_patch and\n_populate_patch_list do not call scroll_visible() after changing the\nindex, so keyboard navigation can also move the selection off-screen.\n\n(via https://msgid.link/2c1ab8a2-8a86-48a7-9a53-ef3a00ab4bd2@csamuel.org)","files":null}]}